## Early-Stage Production-First Policy

This repository runs in early-stage shipping mode. Follow these rules unless explicitly superseded in `AGENTS.md`.

1. Completed changes must be pushed directly to `main` in the same work session.
2. Do not batch completed work into deferred release branches.
3. Production deploy path is `.github/workflows/deploy-ssm.yml` only.
4. After push to `main`, verify deploy workflow success and production health endpoint returns 200:
   - `https://practica.jpagan.com/health/`
5. If deployment fails, apply fix-forward immediately with a new commit to `main`.

## Required Agent Behavior

- Default delivery branch for completed work: `main`.
- Default release strategy: continuous direct-to-production.
- Verification is mandatory, not optional:
  - local minimum validation (frontend build and backend check when environment exists),
  - deploy workflow success,
  - production health success.

## Policy Change Protocol

If release strategy changes (for example PR-only, staging gates, release branches), update:

- `AGENTS.md` (policy + runbook),
- `.cursor/rules.yaml`,
- this file.

All three must change in the same commit.
